# UX Design & Frontend Standards

All UX design and frontend code MUST follow [docs/design-ux-standards.md](../docs/design-ux-standards.md).

## Before Writing Frontend Code

1. Read `docs/design-ux-standards.md` for the full spec
2. Use Design Tokens (colors, spacing, typography, shadows) — no hardcoded values
3. Follow component specs (Button, Input, Card, Modal, Toast, Skeleton)
4. Implement loading, error, and empty states per the doc
5. Ensure a11y: keyboard nav, aria-labels, color contrast ≥ 4.5:1
6. Use `@media (hover: hover)` for PC-only hover effects
7. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for animations

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Colors from tokens (`primary`, `success`, `error`, etc.)
- [ ] Spacing: `spacing-4` / `gap-6` / `py-20` per breakpoints
- [ ] Buttons: verb-first copy, loading spinner, disabled state
- [ ] Images: `alt` attribute; icon buttons: `aria-label`
- [ ] Responsive: Mobile (<640px), Tablet (768–1023px), Desktop (≥1024px)
- [ ] Modal on mobile → bottom Sheet; min touch target 44×44px
